  "executive_brief_md": "## CBLB \u2014 Cbl proto-oncogene B\n\n**White Space score 29.83/100 \u00b7 rank 8/13 \u00b7 MEDIUM confidence.** Mid-cohort \u2014 real biology with moderate competition; watch the momentum trend.\n\nCBLB is a cytoplasm target in the immuno-oncology cohort with no approved drug yet. Development level **Tchem**; mechanism: no ChEMBL-registered mechanism yet. Competitive footprint: no registered industry sponsors. Leading disease associations: hypothyroidism, urticaria, myxedema, multiple sclerosis.\n\n**Score decomposition** \u2014 Validation 0.4972, Tractability 0.6, Saturation 0.0 (cohort-normalized). The score is multiplicative, so crowding drives it down even when biology is validated \u2014 which is why saturated checkpoints sit low and validated-but-uncrowded targets rise.\n\n*Every figure above resolves to a versioned source in the Provenance tab. This brief is model-written (claude-fable-5) over sourced facts only.*",
